title: Nina Paley: Death of the Firstborn Egyptians
description:
I uploaded this exceptionally beautiful video to entice you to watch my interview with its creator, Nina Paley, which is now available on my YouTube channel at: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JyONgwyKEGA

written, directed, designed, animated, produced, etc. by Nina Paley sedermasochism.com/
music from "Spider Suite" by The Duke of Uke and His Novelty Orchestra dukeofukeandhisnoveltyorchestra.bandcamp.com/album/aprils-empire
sound effects by Greg Sextro, eastwestaudio.com/


More of Paley's work can be found at https://vimeo.com/user2983855, including other animations from Exodus, which are being compiled into a feature length film entitled Sedermasochism (see sedermasochism.com)

transcript_parts.text: The falling stars you wished upon
are cinders now and now they're gone.
Their residue festoons my fetid field.
Revealing husks of lovers past,
their shells are all that ever last--
I've taken everything that they've concealed.
Whoever told you life was fair?
Look around you everywhere,
the cruelty of Nature is displayed.
Why the scorn? Why the surprise?
Everything that's born must die
and it isn't I who made the world that way.
What wicked little twist of fate
placed you here upon my plate?
Here where no one hears your cries?
Where was your God to steer you through?
Perhaps your God's forsaken you?
Otherwise, why lead you here to die?
I know the way how,
I'll melt away now.
I know the way.
I'm feeling bliss now,
dissolved to mist, how strangely I go away.
Now I finally know...
It's merely moments now,
moments now until your feeble flesh bends to my will--
and it will, so rest your weary head.
There'll be no pain, no pain at all,
as everything you are dissolves.
Your fate resolved upon my silky threads.
